oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Leila Shute Tigert and unidentified woman looking over their shoulders
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of two women in white dresses with their backs to camera, looking over their shoulders. The woman on the left is Leila Shute Tigert.

Leila Shute (1868-1952) was one of the four daughters of William and Lavinia Shute. She married Dr. Holland McTyeire Tigert (1880-1948) in approximately 1901. The Tigerts lived at Grassmere and Leila oversaw the running of the farm after her father died.
